      "suppliers": [],
      "key_findings": "Resmetirom (REZDIFFRA®) is the FIRST FDA-approved THR-β agonist for MASH/NASH (Mar 14, 2024). MAESTRO-NASH Phase 3 trial showed 25.9-29.9% NASH resolution vs 9.7% placebo (p<0.001), and 24.2-25.9% fibrosis improvement vs 14.2% placebo (p<0.001). Secondary endpoints: LDL-C reduction -13.6% to -16.3%, hepatic fat reduction -34.9% to -38.6%. FDA designations: Breakthrough Therapy, Fast Track, Priority Review. 373+ PubMed publications. EMA approved August 2025.",
      "data_quality": "verified",
      "notes": "FDA Approved Mar 14, 2024. First treatment for NASH/MASH with liver fibrosis (F2-F3). Brand name: REZDIFFRA®. 80mg and 100mg oral tablets, once daily. Most common AEs: diarrhea (23-33%), nausea (15-18%)."
    },
